<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12818#M12818">126</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1688 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div>CLASS: Zerk
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP: Mega important&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>Mana: Useless&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>Endurance: Moderately important<br>AC: Nice to have, but its an individual choice best settled via augs. <br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP Regen: Moderately useless&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>Mana Regen: Insanely infinitely useless<br>Endurance Regen: A few more would be nice, especially post rezz.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Strength: Grrr bark growl better be maxed<br>Stamina: Yep, max me too<br>Agility: Yep, max me too<br>Dexterity: Yep, max me too<br>Charisma: As long as you can hit 110 yer good enough, anything after that is gravy <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br>Intelligence: Um, whats this do?<br>Wisdom: Common sense is for people who dont wield big axes<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Cold Resist: Average (Meaning, I like my resists, but Zerk items dont need to sacrifice other stuff to gain resists)<br>Disease Resist: Average<br>Poison Resist: Average<br>Magic Resist: Average<br>Fire Resist: Average<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Attack: Once its maxed, I r a happy zerk<br>Delay: We use 2 handers, anything over 28 is good nuff for me.<br>Damage: Where its at, baby.<br>Range: Um, we could use 80 more range on our summoned throwing axes, is the microphone on?<br> </div>
<div>Haste: Unless yer increasing the cap, haste is fine the way it is.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Combat Effects: Next to useless...our aas have set proc rates, and most Zerks only have one proc, aa and incidental item CE is gud enough.<br>Shielding: Pretty gosh darn useful. <br>Stun Resist: Just as useful, if not more so than Shielding...less stuns, more damage, or consequently easier time tanking stuff<br>Strikethrough: Once its maxed its all ya can ask for, especially when yer tanking stuff.<br>Spell Shield: Semi useless, nice to have some on the high end but not worth sacrificing anything over<br>Avoidance: Max it out. Keep it maxed. Avoidance is sexy.<br>Accuracy: The key stat for Zerks, imo. 2h are by nature inaccurate beasts, the more of this you have, the better off you are.<br>DOT Shielding: Semi useful, on the high end....mitigates a lil bit of the damage you inflict on yourself via disc.<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
Skill Mods: Frenzy, please add a few more items to the +frenzy list.<br>Click Effects: I like the current crop of clickies available out there, although I wouldnt mind a minotaur illusion clicky.<br>Proc Effects: You guys introduced a heal over time aug for the 50 and below crowd, lets take that idea and bring it to the level 70 crowd. Rune augs would be nice to see too, on the DoN vendors.<br>Worn Effects: Maybe a few select items add regen endurance, otherwise things are pretty sexy where they are.<br>Focus Effects: Bubbling rage line....make more stuff with it. We have a very limited choice in that regard, and a high end zerk has to pretty much sacrifice high end gloves and use Qvic gloves.<br> <div></div>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
