			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12819#M12819">127</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1678 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>As a high-end raiding monk these are what I look at, in order, when I see a link of the loot we just dropped:</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>1) Combat Effects, Accuracy, and Avoidance.&nbsp; These are the prime stats for me and are where my eyes go first.</P>
<P>2) Magic Resist.&nbsp; Deplorably lacking on monk gear.&nbsp; Unbuffed, my MR ranges from 97 - 219 points below my other unbuffed resists.&nbsp; There was a time recently when&nbsp;I was upgrading a few final Time pieces up to Tacvi and Anguish level and 4 upgrades in a row hit me with 10-20 point MR reductions... each.</P>
<P>3) Clicky Effect.&nbsp; Though rare on monk items and in general, I'm always on the look-out for something useful.&nbsp; More overhaste clicks that don't come off of Expansion Head Bosses plz.&nbsp; And I'd like to see more Eternal Ward type clickies than the 2 (I think only 2?) that are avable now.</P>
<P>4) Hit Points.</P>
<P>5) Focus effects, such as Improved Dodge, Improved Block, Ferocity, or Cleave.&nbsp; I'm still looking for an Improved Block item (only 7 in the whole game ?!), and the chance to upgrade a 5 to a 6 on another focus would be taken if other&nbsp;bonuses were&nbsp;on the item&nbsp;too.</P>
<P>6) Secondary Effects such as Strikethrough, Shielding, DoT Shielding, Stun Resist, Spell Shielding.&nbsp; These are all either difficult to cap for monks, or they aren't worth making gear choices over anyway because theyre so easy to cap.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Weapons:&nbsp; </P>
<P>1) I look, first, to make sure it is a one-handed weapon.&nbsp; All 2 handers for monks are inferior to one hander combinations from even previous expansions.&nbsp; Because monks dual wield nearly 100% of the time we can, for practical purposes, add together the damage/delay ratio of our weapons to determine what an equivalent 2 hander would need to have to match its dps.&nbsp; This means that we would need a 2 hander better than current 2.0 weapons for berserkers/pallies/sks for it to be a viable weapon path.</P>
<P>2) Damage/Delay ratio.&nbsp; Is it better than my current non-2.0 weapon? Probably not by much since melee weapons have stagnated since OOW.&nbsp; I'm still using Fangs of The Serpent from Corruption Trial and have passed up many, many, many other one-handers because their ratio is only a hair better.</P>
<P>3) Does it have a lifetap proc? I've been using 4 lifetap procs for a long time now and with 90 CE it parses to around 2000hp a minute.&nbsp; I will probably never loot another weapon that doesn't have an innate lifetap on it.&nbsp; Give us back Serpent's Bite, in an upgraded form.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Also, a general gripe about itemization:</P>
<P>Please please please, give us a reason to use a 2-handed weapon for something other than 18 seconds of Destructive Force when I pull a train of light blues.&nbsp; And, until you do, lower the drop rates of all 2 handers in the game from Anguish and above.&nbsp; Any class with a one-handed 2.0 can't use the generic 2 handers that drop off of every other mob for dps.&nbsp; Any class with a 2-handed 2.0 already has access to a better 2 hander anyway, and thus we hand them out to bots, and eval warriors who dont have 2.0 and NBOB yet.&nbsp; Rikkukan does not need to drop 2 Clawhammers at one.&nbsp; Vish does not need to drop 2 of his staves at once.&nbsp; Yar'Lir doesn't need to drop 2 Katanas at once.&nbsp; Stop giving us so many useless 2 handers!!!&nbsp; </P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1101985>Draclor</a><br><a
							</div>
								
