<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12826#M12826">133</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1603 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Shadow Knight, 70 + 330AA, casual<BR><BR><STRONG>1. AC&nbsp; - The all important stat for plate tanks<BR>2. Shielding - increases tanking ability<BR>3. Avoidance - increases tanking ability</STRONG></P>
<P>4. Stun Resist, Spell Shield, DoT Shielding - important secondary effects</P>
<P>5. Hit Points - More Hit Points&nbsp;=&nbsp;better tank</P>
<P>6a.&nbsp;Melee Focii:<BR>- Improved Parry/Dodge<BR>- +% Mods<BR>- Haste<BR>- Cleave/Ferocity<BR><BR>6b. Spell Focii:<BR>- Detrimental Mana Preservation<BR>- Damage Focus (Magic - 1, Disease - 2, Poison - 3,&nbsp;General for Harm Touch - 4)<BR>- Extended Range<BR>- Extended Detrimental Duration<BR><BR>7. Everything Else (Strikethrough, Mana-regen, Combat Effects), except...</P>
<P>8. Resists... so many resists and yet so many mobs that just cast through them... keeping them high is nice, but the only thing I'd trade for them is...</P>
<P>9. Stats... with diminishing returns on stats, an artificial and annoying to raise stat cap, and already high stat items... they're neglected as any part of gear choice/desirability.</P>
<P>NOTES:</P>
<P>- Clickies add in a fun-factor or usefulness that can potentially trump all of the above, but do not make up for full-time defensive mods (AC/shielding/avoidance/etc...).&nbsp; Inventory clickies = the win!</P>
<P>- Weapons, For a 1-hander, I look for the weapon with the best AC, a useful proc (lifetap, rune, aggro), and finally, it's DPS.&nbsp; Personally, I prefer slower weapons with higher damage to avoid more ripostes.&nbsp; For 2-handers, the best DPS I can find.</P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
