			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>What the other shadowknights have said has been dead on, especially Naubi and Twinkletoes.</P>
<P>We'd invite you to /join serverwide.sk:sk and chat with shadowknights online frequently about shadowknight itemization, similar to how Ngreth and Maddoc chat online in channel serverwide.eqtraders:eqtraders about tradeskills.&nbsp; They're excellent at customer service because they take the time to chat with the customer.&nbsp; This is how you'd make sure that you were in touch with the portion of the shadowknight community that doesn't visit these boards.</P>
<P>Please fix the AC on Umbral Plate Faceguard, the shadowknight only face item from demiplanes.&nbsp; I'm not demiplane flagged and still this is important to me.&nbsp; It would be nice to have something to look forward to that's more ac than my current plane of time mask.</P>
<P>CLASS: SHADOWKNIGHT</P>
<DIV>HP: Less important than AC by a factor of ten.&nbsp; Still somewhat important though.<BR>Mana: Generally not a factor in gear decisions.<BR>Endurance: Unimportant.<BR>AC: Once shielding and avoidance are capped, this is THE MOST IMPORTANT STAT for sk's.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>HP Regen: Important at low levels, unimportant at high levels.<BR>Mana Regen: Moderately important.<BR>Endurance Regen: Not important.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Strength: Important at low levels, not important at high levels.<BR>Stamina: Important at low levels, not important at high levels.<BR>Agility: Important to keep over 75.&nbsp; Important at low levels, not important at high levels.<BR>Dexterity: Important at low levels, not important at high levels.<BR>Charisma: Important at high levels, not important at low levels.<BR>Intelligence: Important for mana pool, learning tradeskills, etc.&nbsp; Reasonably important at all levels.<BR>Wisdom: Never useful for anything, should NOT be on shadowknight only gear.&nbsp; EVER.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cold Resist: Somewhat important.<BR>Disease Resist: Somewhat important.<BR>Poison Resist: Somewhat important.<BR>Magic Resist: Very important to resist charm spells and mez spells.<BR>Fire Resist: Somewhat important.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Attack: Useful for groups, not very useful for raids.<BR>Delay: Not a significant factor, ratio is more important.<BR>Damage: Bigger damage is better, we like the eye candy from large crits.&nbsp; But still ratio is best.<BR>Range: Very big range for pulling.</DIV>
<DIV>Haste: Would be nice to have haste on high ac gear.&nbsp; I use tribute haste currently.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Combat Effects: Somewhat important.&nbsp; More useful for warriors than for sk's.&nbsp; Not a factor in gear choices.<BR>Shielding: Important to cap.&nbsp; Probably the most important stat if not capped.<BR>Stun Resist: Not a factor in gear decisions.&nbsp; Nice, but not critical to have.<BR>Strikethrough: Not a factor in gear decisions.&nbsp; Also nice, but also not critical to have.<BR>Spell Shield: Important.&nbsp; I work on this when I can, if it doesn't mess up my AC.<BR>Avoidance: Important to cap.&nbsp; Second to shielding in importance.<BR>Accuracy: Not a factor in gear decisions.&nbsp; Nice, but not critical to have.<BR>DOT Shielding: Somewhat important.&nbsp; Less so than shielding, avoidance, spell shielding.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Skill Mods: 2hs and 1hs skill mod would be nice.&nbsp; Dodge, parry, riposte skill mods are useful.&nbsp; But none will be a factor in gear decisions, for the most part.<BR>Click Effects: FUN!!&nbsp; We love these, they make the game fun.<BR>Proc Effects: These can be fun too.&nbsp; Their effect on how well we tank is what's important.<BR>Worn Effects: Improved dodge, improved parry, ferocity, cleave, faerune are all nice to have.<BR>Focus Effects: Detrimental mana preservation, extended detrimental (DOT length), magic focus, poison focus, disease focus, harmtouch focus, lifetap focus are all useful focuses to have, and in many cases I make gear decisions based on the focus effects.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Please make high end shadowknight items have a poison focus instead of a healing focus.&nbsp; Demiplane plate items have healing focus effects on them -- ZERO use to shadowknights, only useful for clerics or paladins.&nbsp; Give us some stuff with poison focus on them, or put both healing and poison focus on the items so that it's useful for us if we're plate wearers who don't cast heal spells.&nbsp; There's no upgrade in game currently that I know of for the poison focus on my earring from inktu'ta, the Earhoop of the Eighteen Eyes.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							[img]http://www.strike9.com/Bolas/noobiebeggers.gif[/img]
[url=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=429220]Duke Bolas Bonesmith - Dread Lord[/url]
							</div>
								
