Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12833#M12833">140</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1482 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			(excellent &gt; good &gt; average &gt; low &gt; /ignore)<br>
<br>
CLASS: DRUID
<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>HP: excellent<br>Mana: excellent<br>Endurance: /ignore<br>AC: average (after we hit a certain AC, does it really matter anymore?)<br>
 </div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>HP Regen: average<br>Mana Regen: excellent<br>Endurance Regen: /ignore<br>
 </div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>Strength: average<br>Stamina: good<br>Agility: /ignore<br>Dexterity: /ignore<br>Charisma: low (useful at vendors)<br>Intelligence: /ignore<br>Wisdom: excellent<br>
 </div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>Cold Resist: good<br>Disease Resist: good (I've always noticed that my disease resist is ALWAYS lower than the others, fire/ice/magic/poison)<br>Poison Resist: good<br>Magic Resist: good<br>Fire Resist:good </div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>Attack: /ignore<br>Delay: /ignore<br>Damage: /ignore<br>Range:/ignore </div>

<div>Haste:/ignore </div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>Combat Effects: /ignore<br>Shielding: average - nice but it doesn't help us that much. best to not get hit.<br>Stun Resist: good<br>Strikethrough: /ignore<br>Spell Shield: excellent<br>Avoidance: excellent<br>Accuracy: /ignore<br>DOT Shielding:excellent </div>

<div>&nbsp;</div><u>

Skill Mods:</u><br><br>would be nice to see mods for: dodge, alteration, evocation, conjuration.&nbsp; dodge because it's nice to avoid getting hit.&nbsp; the schools of magic because&nbsp; of its potential mana savings (other than mana pres focus).&nbsp; the benefits of other class skills are unknown to me but consider: channeling, track, meditation.<br><br><u>
Click Effects:<br><br></u>I like my epic clicky (DoT) and my resist clicky.&nbsp; I haven't got too many of them though.&nbsp; They are nice but they shouldn't overwhelm the player (by having multiple 'must have' clickies)<br><br><u>
Proc Effects:</u><br>/ignore<br><br><u>
Worn Effects:</u><br>Want more avoidance and improved dodge please!&nbsp; stun resist is nice.&nbsp; it seems there are healthy amounts of gear for all three shielding types but ones with avoidance, dodge modifiers, and improved dodge are rare (unless they are supposed to be?)<br><br><br><u>
Focus Effects:<br></u>here it kind of gets tough being a druid, we need to collect beneficial AND detrimental focus effects (as with other classes).&nbsp; it's a real chore to pick all of these foci up.&nbsp; the foci are broken down into each type<br>direct damage<br>&nbsp;- fire<br>&nbsp;- ice<br>&nbsp;- magic<br><br>dots<br>&nbsp;- fire<br>&nbsp;- magic<br><br>then the beneficial/detrimental part of every basic focus effect: mana pres, extended duration, spell haste, etc.<br><br>manage all that plus resists/all shielding types/avoidance/stun resist/etc<br><br>it's a bit much.&nbsp; the lists of this gear have gotten more complicated as time goes on.&nbsp; I like having options but I think things need to be pulled in a tad.&nbsp; <br><br>It's hard to talk about this because I don't have a resource to look all this info up - as it's spread out amongst the web.&nbsp; I speak as a semi-casual raider that is real close to breaking into anguish.<br><br>Thank you for your time.<br>	
		</td></tr>
