<hr>
Fzan_Torv wrote:<br>
<div><br>I think it's terribly terribly dangerous to ask US what we feel is important and then to use that in any way to balance items.<br></div>
<hr>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, this isn't a democracy, but as the benevolent dictator of
itemization, I don't think it can hurt to give some consideration to
the thoughts of players... Just because I take the time to listen,
doesn't mean I'll agree with everything I hear. I do think it will
allow me to make more educated decisions, which I think is a good
thing. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></p><br><hr></blockquote>I can't stand stats in RPGs. I know
they are part of the mechanism, but to me it's like going to the
theater and being able to see the wires on Peter Pan. They have to be
there but I shouldn't have to see them, let alone study them.<br>
