<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12836#M12836">143</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1433 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P><FONT size=3>Many thanks&nbsp;Merloc for taking the time to talk with us!</FONT></P><FONT size=2>
<P><FONT size=3>I've been playing this enchanter as my main since 2000.&nbsp; I've gone the old school route from the newbie zones through the old world, began raiding withVox, did the whole trek through NTOV and Ssra and PoP. My guild right now is about to enter Tacvi and working on MPG trials and DoD curse raids.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3>One frustration I have with itemization is that enchanters are lumped in with other casters. Every item that drops has mana, FT and spell shield on it. Now don't get me wrong; I do need that stuff. But the enchanter is a class that gets beat on and what I need most of all is surviveability. A big mana pool is worthless when I am dead.. So in gear I look for HP, I looked for avoidance but right now I am 30 over the cap; now I am looking for Shielding and I can't find it on much caster gear and when all/all items come up the loot council gives them to the tanks.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3>In my view, an enchanter's job is to control adds until a tank can get around to them. With recent expansions, this has become tougher and tougher to do, and itemization is just one part of that. The ramping up of the damage on mobs in recent expansions means that off-tanking&gt;mezzing and pulling&gt;incamp crowd control. </FONT></P>
<P><FONT size=3>To quote Yakk's excellent post on TheRunes,</FONT></P></FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P align=left><FONT face="Times New Roman"><EM><FONT size=3>Tanks take on the order of 75% less DPS in the same content that enchanters do. They get hit half as often, and they take half as much damage per hit.<BR><BR>This ratio -- 4 times less damage -- is what causes the survivability problem. In challenging content, the tank cannot survive without timely healing -- which means in gear-appropriate challenging content, enchanters cannot survive even with timely healing.<BR><BR>Tanks deserve to be the most effective at tanking NPCs. However, in the current state of the game, it is only in content that is trivial that an enchanter can risk letting themselves be hit. </FONT></EM></FONT></P></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT face=Arial size=3>My biggest frustration is that even when I improve my gear, it hardly seems to make any difference. When I moved from Time to Qvic gear I could see an improvement in&nbsp;old world zones like farming the&nbsp;PoP&nbsp;Planes.&nbsp; But in&nbsp;an MPG raid I get slapped down&nbsp;so fast I don't have time to react.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;My class&nbsp;needs tuning ... and &nbsp;appropriate itemization would be a&nbsp;great start.</FONT></P>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Newar Chryalis of Xev<br>Bedazzler of Seofon<br>Druzzil Ro
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
