			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12837#M12837">144</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1429 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><FONT size=2>
<P>That said: On to the questionaire:</P>
<P>CLASS: ENCHANTER</P>
<P>HP: Awesome. I am getting close to 11k raid buffed and that is no where near enough. It means I can survive maybe long enough to get off a second mez on a resist. Given silk class awful damage mitigation, my lust for HP is endless.</P>
<P>Mana: Important. More is good, but I rarely get in trouble because I am low on mana; it's more likely that I die with lots of reserves. All the gear at my level comes with nice mana upgrades and I don't have to seek it out special. I pass on mana augs. Usually I only run low when chain nuking, which is not a critical function, and then I have Gather Mana in reserve.</P>
<P>Endurance: Irrelevant.</P>
<P>AC: My understanding is that the AC soft cap for my class is around 1000, around 1300 with all defensive AAs maxed (which I have. I've acquired 1300 AC without having to seek out special gear to get it . . .with the one exception of looking for more AC for my shield where it would make a difference. I would dearly love to see the AC soft cap raised for my class. </P>
<P>HP regen: Okay. It doesn't regen fast enough to make a difference. In groups/raids I am being healed. Solo, it might cut the downtime a bit, but I'll probably just drink a potion.</P>
<P>Mana regen: Important. . . or it was until I got it capped. FT is easy to get. I had FT on gear capped about a year ago. I found I getting the Girdle of Efficiency with Maelin's Methodical Mind clickie was a godsend, allowing me to stretch my mana pool much further and recover much faster after a tough fight and solo much longer. Getting my FT aura spell is giving me similar joy.</P>
<P>Endurance regen: Irrelevant.</P>
<P>Pretty much all my base stats are capped at my gear level.</P>
<P>Strength: irrelevant except in a zone like Uqua. It mattered some at starting levels since Erudites are weak. I tradeskill, so if I can get an overstrength buff I can drive my STR higher than my INT for tradeskill checks.</P>
<P>Stamina = more hit points, which makes it important, but mine is over cap now.</P>
<P>Agility = less hits, but it is a small effect and mine is over cap now.</P>
<P>Dexterity: Only use I have found is for tradeskills... affects tailoring and jewelcraft. Overdex buff like Wunshi allows me to drive my DEX higher than my INT while doing combines.</P>
<P>Charisma: Important. This is the only one I worry about. It helps on charm duration and mezz resists and those are crucial. I go over cap using my CHA buff but I'd sure like that to come from gear and free up a buff slot. High end CHA gear seems somewhat rare.</P>
<P>Intelligence: Okay. An important stat, but I am way way way over the cap and have been for years.</P>
<P>Wisdom: Irrelevant.</P>
<P>All resists are good. My guild is raiding a lot in zones with nasty AE's. Any way I can prevent those effects from hurting me is good.</P>
<P>I try to keep my resists balanced as much as possible. I don't specifically choose gear for a single type of resist; I look for total resists. I may try to boost the lowest one. I may pass up an item which is otherwise good if it means losing resists. I may take a weaker item with lots of resists. For example, finally got the Ancient Werewolf Skull with the 50 to all resist clickie, which is one of my most prized possessions. Am wearing it now to level it up, taking a significant hit on hp/mana and other stats temporarily.</P>
<P>Attack: meh. Only useful when soloing. I managed to get Despair, which I have auged with a cold proc aug, for when I want to go toe-to-toe with greens/lt blues, mostly tradeskill farming.</P>
<P>Delay: irrelevant</P>
<P>Damage: Meh. Only matters when soloing.</P>
<P>Range: irrelevant. Now spell range, that's another matter.</P>
<P>Haste: Meh. Only matters with soloing; I keep a battered Luclin Shield of Infused Power with 41% haste to go with Despair when I am farming.</P>
<P>Combat effects: irrelevant</P>
<P>Shielding: Important. I went for Avoidance first but I am over cap now. Shielding is not as effective but it is almost impossible to come by on caster gear. Right now I have only 6 shielding while boasting 21 spell sheild and 20 dot shield. And that is not for lack of trying to get it. Itemization does not put shielding on caster gear and my guild's loot council will not award it to a caster until every mele in the guild has it. Since surviveability is my #1 priority, this is frustrating.</P>
<P>Stun resist: Awesome. Absolutely essential to be able to fire off mezzes, stuns and charms while being beat on. I have 17 stun resist now and I want more more more.</P>
<P>Strikethrough: irrelevant.</P>
<P>Spell Shield: Important. Not as crucial to an enchanter as some other casters because we get protection from our rune and alendar spells. But still very needed for high end raiding. But it is also easy to find. Most caster gear comes with some spell shield. I have 21 points now without even trying to get it.</P>
<P>Avoidance: Awesome. I've spent the last 6 months on a quest for Avoidance gear, often passing up even large hp upgrades. However now I'm 30 over the cap. Avoidance is wonderful but not rare.</P>
<P>Accuracy: Irrelevant</P>
<P>Dot Shielding: Awesome. Very much needed in some of the raiding my guild is doing now in GoD. My runes don't provide the protection against dots that they do for DDs, so that makes it more needed. And also seems harder to find on gear than Spell Shield. I am at 20 now and looking for more.</P>
<P>Skill mods: Meh. These often seem to provide very small benefits. The exception is tradeskill mods. I am working on the full line of the PoR tradeskill trophies.</P>
<P>Click effects: Awesome, depending what they are of course. I carry a bagful with me always. Ancient Werewolf Skull for clickie resists, Girdle of Efficiency for clickie FT,</P>
<P>epic 1.5 for clickie rune, epic 1.0 for clickie haste, Armguard of Purity for clickie poison cure, Charmweaver Robe for clickie Magic debuff, blue ceramic band for clickie small nuke, Goblin Gazughi Ring for clickie charm break. I yearn for Memory and SoV and a clickie shrink (got tinkered one) and a clickie annul magic item. I had a 100-point clickie heal earring which I retired; would love a decent click heal or hot; use tons of potions. Would die for a clickie snare.</P>
<P>Proc effects: Meh. I don't mele much and when I do it is more than a joke cause I do so little dps. When farming solo I will equip a weapon with procs, just because my dps sucks so bad any little bit helps.</P>
<P>Worn effects: Important, depending what they are. Faerune is very valuable to me... with an Erudite's poor vision I can't duplicate that with AAs. I paid out a ton of plat to make an Improved Dodge 3 Aug. I have several Innoruk's </P>
<P>Focus effects: Awesome, depending what they are. As some others have commented, managing to acquire all the foci needed by a caster on a piece of gear that can work as a set with other foci is a challenge and a puzzle. Itemization needs to consider not only what the focus is but what slots it can be worn in and what other foci may be displaced to equip the item. I am playing this game now.</P>
<P>I have Detrimental Extension focus on Fracade of Fright. I need this. I have the Ancient Werewolf Mask but I can't properly equip that until I have found a Detrimental Extension focus that fits in another slot. So the Werewolf is bagged much of the time. I am told that when my guild gets to Tacvi there is a belt that drops with Detrimental Extension on it. But my belt is Girdle of Efficiency and I can't live without that. So I can't upgrade that belt till I find another item with Maelin's Methodical Mind or equivelent. Working on making a bazu aug to try to solve this puzzle.</P>
<P>Foci for enchanter that I look for, in order of importance:</P>
<P>Detrimental mana conservation</P>
<P>Detrimental spell haste</P>
<P>Beneficial mana conservation</P>
<P>Detrimental range</P>
<P>Detrimental extension</P>
<P>Increase spell damage (magic or chromatic) </P>
<P>Beneficial extension</P>
<P>Others are not important.</P>
<P>I have an old Innoruk's Sarcasm item which I rarely equip because it is only 120 hp/mana. I would very much like to find this focus at my gear level.</P>
<P>I do not have any damage focus for my chromatic nuke, and I would dearly like to get hold of one.</P>
<P>I got a Reagant Conservation focus in Plane of Time which was useless to me because it capped at level 65 spells. I can't find any that will work on my level 69 Rune of Rikkuken. I go through a stack of peridots every day I play and more at raids casting this Rune.</P>
<P>I would be very interested in seeing items with Rune foci as others have suggested.</P></FONT></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Newar Chryalis of Xev<br>Bedazzler of Seofon<br>Druzzil Ro
							</div>
								
