		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<P>Class: Berserker , Lvl 70, Demiplane + raiding</P>
<P>Instead of listing everything, I will just touch on what most of our small community agree's is important or could use some tweaking.</P>
<P>HP: High, as pure DPS we need a lot of padding for the occaisional aggro.</P>
<P>Endurance: Very High. This is our bread and butter to performing well and sustaining our DPS</P>
<P>Endurance Regen: Most important. In current form, this is laughable at best. Adding some type of click effect along the line of Jester Wine to an armor item, minus the HP regen and you have a major winner. Somewhere around +5 END regen would be a&nbsp;tremendous improvement.</P>
<P>Attack: Important to us, but easily obtainable via augments and current items.</P>
<P>Accuracy: High, obvios reasons. The more we hit, the better we are doing our one and only job.... DPS.</P>
<P>Focus effects: High. Blistering Rage needs more itemization, if not a new level beyond 20% increase. Most of us are tired of using Qvic gloves at our current level. An augment perhaps to allow us to upgrade?</P>
<P>Skill mods: High. An addition of Throwing % modifiers could be an excellent substitute if no more throwing foci are to be added for us. Berserkers are the masters of throwing after all.</P>
<P>Delay/Damage: Very important as we can only use 2 handed weapons. I echo Swampfunk.. if the ratio is rockin' I'm happy.</P>
<P>Weapon Procs: How about a nice jolt proc for aggro reduction?</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Rageheart Maelliv</P>
<P>Berserker of Dragon Council</P>	
