			>
			CLASS: Beastlord
<div>RACE: Barbarian<br>LEVEL: 70<br>Play Style: Family Guild, Occasional Raid, Solo/Group about 60/40<br>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP: High<br>Mana: Med-High<br>Endurance: Low <br>AC: High<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>HP Regen: Med-High  <br>Mana Regen: Med-High<br>Endurance Regen: Low<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Strength: Med-Low<br>Stamina: Med-High<br>Agility: Med-Low<br>Dexterity: High<br>Charisma: Low<br>Intelligence: Low<br>Wisdom: Med-High<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Cold Resist: Medium<br>Disease Resist: Medium<br>Poison Resist: Medium<br>Magic Resist: Medium<br>Fire Resist: Medium<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Attack: Med-High<br>Delay: High<br>Damage: High<br>Range: Low<br> </div>
<div>Haste: High<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div>Combat Effects: High<br>Shielding: Med-High<br>Stun Resist: Med-High<br>Strikethrough: High<br>Spell Shield: Med-High<br>Avoidance: High<br>Accuracy: High<br>DOT Shielding: Med-High<br> </div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
Skill Mods: Med-High<br>Click Effects: High<br>Proc Effects: High<br>Worn Effects: High<br>Focus Effects: High<br><br>As a general rule, when I'm upgrading gear, I tend to go for things that are higher in HP first (for armor) followed by AC and then a stat that I haven't already capped. This usually means Dex for higher proc rate. I am using augs for most of my Combat Effects and Focus Effects improvements, but I would definitely love to upgrade to gear that has those built-in so I could use the aug slots for more HP or to further enhance the effect.<br><br>For weapons, I always look at dmg/dly ratio first, but given the choice I'll opt for whichever has a LIFETAP proc. If there isn't one, I will buy a couple augs for lifetapping goodness.<br> <div></div>	
