<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=12843#M12843">150</a> of 370
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1362 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div><br><blockquote><hr>Merloc-DEV wrote:<br><div></div><br>
<blockquote>
<hr>
Fzan_Torv wrote:<br>
<div><br>I think it's terribly terribly dangerous to ask US what we feel is important and then to use that in any way to balance items.<br></div>
<hr>
</blockquote>
<p>Well, this isn't a democracy, but as the benevolent dictator of itemization, I don't think it can hurt to give some consideration to the thoughts of players... Just because I take the time to listen, doesn't mean I'll agree with everything I hear. I do think it will allow me to make more educated decisions, which I think is a good thing. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></p><br><hr></blockquote><br>I disagree.&nbsp; Educated decisions on what players want items to look like for a tiny subset of the player base, perhaps.&nbsp; Educated decisions on what works best in game comes from knowing how the back-end of the game works, which on the whole, the players only have empirical evidence where-as hopefully you'll have real access to.<br><br>For example, I may think shielding is a critical stat on warrior gear, but you may know that the next expansion has mobs who's DB are so low as to make shielding worthless.&nbsp; High_end_raiding_warrior_001 wants massive HP, Mid_range_raiding_warrior_001 wants more shielding (high end guy is maxed so placed it lower since it's easy to get for him), real_high_end_guy wants avoidance, etc., etc., etc.&nbsp; There's too much variation.&nbsp; I honestly can't believe any weight can be given to the stat opinions of a self&nbsp; selecting subset of a subset of players.<br><br>Ask the class rep's to gather opinion and form a rough consensus per class if you absolutely must, just to get rough ideas, or clearly differentiate the play styles, hard-core-non-raider, hard-core-raider, casual-raider, etc., etc., etc.&nbsp; You've asked a question of say 1000 people to which there are 1000 answers.<br><br>Sorry, I feel really strongly about this.<br></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							-- <br>Lock: "Goddamnit, Morpheus! Not everyone believes what you believe!"<br>Morpheus: "My beliefs do not require them to."
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
